# Onshape Drawings

A **drawing** is a 2D documentation element — orthographic/section/detail views,
dimensions, annotations and a title block — that references parts or assemblies
defined elsewhere in the document. It lives as a tab (`eid`) beside the Part
Studios and Assemblies it documents (@onshape/elements). The drawing itself holds
no geometry: each **view** is a projection of a referenced model, so editing the
model reflows the views. Deliverables (PDF/DWG/DXF) are produced by **exporting**,
which is an async translation job (@onshape/export_translation).

## Model

- Addressed by `did/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}` like any element. **Create** must target
  a workspace (`POST …/d/{did}/w/{wid}/create`); reads accept `w`/`v`/`m`.
- A drawing **references** the models it documents: the create body names the source
  `documentId` + `elementId` (+ `documentMicroversionId`/`elementMicroversionId`,
  `externalDocumentId`/`externalDocumentVersionId` for a cross-document reference)
  plus view options (`border`, `hiddenLines`, `includeSurfaces`, `includeWires`,
  `isFlattenedPart`, `numberHorizontalZones`/`numberVerticalZones`, …). The new
  drawing tab is a distinct `eid` from the part/assembly it draws — see
  @onshape/parts and @onshape/assemblies for the referenced models.
- A **view** (`/views`) is a placed projection; `/views/{viewid}/jsongeometry`
  returns its 2D geometry as JSON (optional `scale`).
- **Export is asynchronous.** `POST …/translations` does not return a file: it
  returns a translation request with an `id` and a `requestState` (e.g. `ACTIVE`).
  Poll `GET /translations/{tid}` until `DONE`, then download the result — the full
  poll+download loop lives in @onshape/export_translation. `translationformats`
  lists what the drawing can be exported to before you ask.
- Drawing edits go through a separate async channel: `POST …/e/{eid}/modify`
  returns a modification request whose progress is read at
  `GET /drawings/modify/status/{mrid}` (`requestState`). This slice exposes no
  endpoint for templates/standards as a standalone resource.

## Endpoints

| METHOD path | purpose |
|---|---|
| `POST /drawings/d/{did}/w/{wid}/create` | Create a drawing in a document (references a model). |
| `POST /drawings/d/{did}/w/{wid}/e/{eid}/modify` | Modify a drawing via a JSON op payload (async). |
| `GET /drawings/d/{did}/w/{wid}/e/{eid}/translationformats` | List formats the drawing can be exported to. |
| `GET /drawings/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/views` | Details of all drawing views. |
| `GET /drawings/d/{did}/{wvm}/{wvmid}/e/{eid}/views/{viewid}/jsongeometry` | One view's geometry as JSON (`scale`). |
| `POST /drawings/d/{did}/{wv}/{wvid}/e/{eid}/translations` | Export (translate) the drawing — async, returns a translation id. |
| `GET /drawings/modify/status/{mrid}` | Status of a `modify` operation. |

All accept `linkDocumentId` (query) where a cross-document reference applies; views
also take `transactionId`/`changeId`.

## Shapes

`GET …/e/{eid}/views` — list of placed views (trimmed):

```json
{
  "changeId": "string",
  "errorCode": 0,
  "errorDescription": "string",
  "items": [ { /* BTAppDrawingViewInfo: per-view placement + metadata */ } ],
  "parentChangeId": "string"
}
```

`POST …/{wv}/{wvid}/e/{eid}/translations` — request body (trimmed) and response.
The response is a **translation request**, not a file:

```json
// body — pick a target format from translationformats
{ "formatName": "PDF", "destinationName": "drawing-export", "currentSheetOnly": false }

// response — async job; id is what you poll
{
  "id": "5f…",
  "requestState": "ACTIVE",
  "documentId": "string",
  "workspaceId": "string",
  "resultDocumentId": "string",
  "resultElementIds": ["string"],
  "resultExternalDataIds": ["string"],
  "href": "https://cad.onshape.com/api/translations/5f…",
  "failureReason": "string"
}
```

When `requestState` reaches `DONE`, `resultExternalDataIds` holds the downloadable
blob id(s) — download per @onshape/export_translation.

## Recipe

Read-first against an existing drawing: list its views and assert the response.
kb2 may have no drawing tab, so this documents the shape and the verify asserts
HTTP 200 + an `items` array (the create→export→poll flow is below it).

```bash
# needs ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY / ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY (Basic auth — local testing only; HMAC in @onshape/auth)
: "${DID:?}" "${WID:?}" "${EID:?}"   # drawing element coordinates from the doc URL
base=https://cad.onshape.com/api/v10

curl -sS -u "$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY" \
  "$base/drawings/d/$DID/w/$WID/e/$EID/views" -o views.json -w '%{http_code}\n'

# verify: 200 and an items array present
python3 - <<'PY'
import json,sys
d=json.load(open("views.json"))
assert isinstance(d.get("items"),list), f"no views[] in response: {d}"
print(f"ok: {len(d['items'])} view(s)")
PY
```

Export (create→translate→poll) — POST returns a translation id, then poll until
`DONE` and download (full loop in @onshape/export_translation):

```bash
# 1. confirm the drawing supports the target format
curl -sS -u "$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY" \
  "$base/drawings/d/$DID/w/$WID/e/$EID/translationformats"

# 2. request the export (async) — capture the translation id
tid=$(curl -sS -u "$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY" \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"formatName":"PDF","destinationName":"drawing-export"}' \
  "$base/drawings/d/$DID/w/$WID/e/$EID/translations" | python3 -c 'import json,sys;print(json.load(sys.stdin)["id"])')
test -n "$tid" && echo "translation id: $tid"   # verify: a non-empty id came back

# 3. poll GET /translations/$tid until requestState == DONE, then download
#    resultExternalDataIds — see @onshape/export_translation
```

To create first, `POST …/d/{did}/w/{wid}/create` with `{documentId, elementId,
drawingName}` (the model to draw) into a **scratch workspace**, read the returned
`id` (the new drawing `eid`), then run the export above against it.

UI fallback (open/export a drawing in the web app): @onshape/playwright.
Related: @onshape/export_translation · @onshape/elements · @onshape/assemblies · @onshape/parts.
